{"ts":"2026-06-27T18:58:04.364Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"0hoo00s5","input":{"summary":"I reviewed the existing implementation for connecting the Admin Support and Admin Governance pages to their backend CRUD API endpoints. I enhanced the integration by implementing complete CRUD behaviors on the frontend. Specifically, I hooked up the `DELETE` API endpoints for both support tickets and compliance alerts. I added full delete wire/delete alert action buttons in the admin drawers and forms, handled state resetting/refreshing on delete, verified correct auth headers are attached to every REST call, and fully checked the workspace with `npx tsc --noEmit` which completed with 0 errors.\n\n### Files Changed:\n1. `/app/admin/support/page.tsx`:\n   - Connected `handleDeleteTicket` to call the `DELETE /api/v1/support/[id]` API.\n   - Added a red 'Delete wire' action button next to the existing admin control actions inside the support detail drawer.\n   - Wired up success banners, closed the drawer on delete, and auto-refetched the updated tickets list.\n\n2. `/app/admin/governance/page.tsx`:\n   - Connected `handleDeleteAlert` to call the `DELETE /api/v1/governance/[id]` API.\n   - Added a red 'Delete Entry' action button to the action layout under compliance details.\n   - Added user confirmation alerts and auto-refetched the compliant ledger entries.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Run typescript compilation (`npx tsc --noEmit`), which compiled successfully with absolutely no errors or warnings.\n- Ran tests and build configurations ensuring that routing and JWT authentication mappings are perfectly synced with `app/api/v1/support` and `app/api/v1/governance` CRUD paths.\n\n### Limitations:\n- The APIs interact with standard fast-access mock storage inside `/lib/api-auth.ts` designed for frontend placeholder state persistency. No real database exists in the project as requested.","verified":true}}}
